text: WHAT A HURDLE BY ZEKE. UFNORTUNATELY LOST HIS BALANCE OR HE WOULD'VE SCORED. NOW IT WILL BE TOUGH. PLAY OF THE YEAR!
I will be surprised if the Cowboys get 7 points out of this.
I like the QB draw call. Just great play by Cox.
Nobody open. But Dak has to throw that away.

Dak doesn't have much protection, hasn't had a receiver who can get open (pre-Amari), hasn't had a consistent run game or play calling ... and his confidence is crumbling. He's getting double-pumping hesitant and gunshy.
Now it feels like the Eagles are saying, OK, enough of this.
Blitz. Force a quick throw. Tackle.
Let Dak run uptempo no-huddle as he did late first half vs Tenn. This is when he's best. Quits second-guessing. Just plants and fires.
That's when Dak is DAK (minus the sack). Just rock and fire. Throw it like he MEANS IT.
If Zeke hadn't lost his balance after that incredible hurdle ...
LeBron must be furious the NBA is making him play the Hawks instead of letting him watch his Cowboys. He needs to speak to the commish about this.
Obviously I was hoping the Cowboys could come out hot on offense and take it home. Instead, THAT happened. You're going to roll to Michael Bennett without blocking him???
I feel like I've already sweated out two games and we're just starting the second half.
If only Dak had an Ertz.
That's it. Kicker has gone south. Huge advantage, Philly. Eagles will be re-inspired. Psychological killer for Cowboys.
Only hope now is a turnover.
Jordan Matthews of Vanderbilt University should be catching passes from Tom Brady.
If only Dallas had an Ertz. Or a Dallas Goedert.
LeBron, only 1 rebound, 1 assist at halftime as Lakers trail Hawks by 1. Mind must be on Cowboys-Eagles.
Rare good play call by Linehan.
Eagles receivers make so many good grabs of wild throws.
THIS IS WAY TOO EASY. COME ON, DEFENSE, OFFENSE GAVE YOU SOME FRONT TO RUN WITH.
HE'S GOING TO THROW IT TO ERTZ ALMOST EVERY CRUCIAL TIME. DOUBLE HIM. FORCE WINCE TO GO ELSEWHERE.
That was just crushing. No pass rush. No run defense. Heath gets smoked. THAT WAS WHERE THE DEFENSE COULD'VE TAKEN A STAND AND TAKEN THE GAME OVER.
I will not accept any "moral victory." In fact, that could be even worse big picture than getting blown out.
He caught it.
Our "Ertz" from Stanford finally caught one and made a little play.
Worth a try. I'll take an overthrow vs an underthrow.
That was a vintage Dak/Zeke road drive for TD. HAVE I EVER MISSED THEM.
PASS RUSH. TURNOVER.
Just one mistake.
Vander Esch made a terrific athletic play. But Jaylon Smith was flying in and would've made the tackle for a short gain at best.
They just had to make this nervous.
HOW BOUT THAT DAK PRESCOTT AND THAT EZEKIEL ELLIOTT! HOW BOUT THAT DEFENSE HOLDING AN OFFENSE WITH FOUR DANGEROUS RECEIVERS TO 20 POINTS AT PHILLY! HOW BOUT CARSON WINCE!

I was so wrong the day after the draft about Leighton Vander Esch. He's long, rangy, athletic and fast with terrific instincts and anticipation. He and Jaylon Smith could be attending Pro Bowls together at some point.
Wonder if "Unc" has downed an extra bottle of Henny to drown the pain? Wonder if Shannon Sharpe, president of the National Cowboy Haters, will show up tomorrow at 9:30 E for Undisputed?

LeBron just LeBricked TWO free throws, one for the win, next for the tie, then Kuzma rebounded and missed and LeBron follow-dunked for a one-point lead. Saved from the ultimate humiliation. 15 secs left.
Tyson Chandler just got away with a goal-tend on Trae Young's last scoop shot.
LeBron James is the worst superstar late-game, close-game free throw shooter ever - his Achilles heel. Never seen anything like it.
Do I think the Cowboys can win at Atlanta and beat the Saints? NO. But do I feel way better about this team? YES. I'm going to bask in this for one whole week.
I despise the Philadelphia Eagles. That was as satisfyingly unexpected a win as I can ever remember. CryEaglesCry.

As a Cowboy fan, I sure hope the Eagles don't go back to Nick Foles. That would be trouble for Dallas and Washington.

I do feel sorry for Odell stuck with a washed-up Eli. Yes, Odell got paid to grin and bear it - he's the NFL's highest paid receiver. But just now he should've had a big bomb TD on MNF and Eli underthrew him by 10 yards.
Odell should've caught that slant from Eli.
Absurd pass interference saved the Giants. DB didn't turn to look for the ball. But Odell didn't see it either and didn't even try for it.

I will say Eli threw the ball much better on that final drive, with more conviction and velocity and accuracy. He always does just enough to make the Giants and their fans think, "Well, maybe he's still got some left." Don't be fooled.

In Jimmy Butler's debut, Sixers blow a 16-point 4th q lead at Orlando and lose. Jimmy was hesitant to take over and close. That must change. Embiid had his 1st career trip-dub but fell in love with jumpers late instead of attacking, shooting FTs. This team will grow from this.
Joel Embiid is the best player in the East. But he doesn't always choose the wisest shots.

If the Warriors trust DCousins health the second half of this season, they should trade Draymond. More trouble than he's worth. Salvage this season and increase chances KD stays, at least next year. Draymond called KD a name you can't take back.

Warriors just don't look right. Only 41 first-half points. Still awkward and icy between KD and Draymond. Unfixable. Will keep bubbling to surface. This is good news for the West, especially for the LeLakers.
Blind Witnesses: You're really throwing a parade for LeBron for passing Wilt Chamberlain on the scoring list? LeBron has played 112 more games than Wilt did!

I project LeBron will pass The Greatest Player ever on the scoring list in 32 more games, on Thursday night, Jan. 17 in (fittingly) my hometown of OKC. On that night, LeBron will have played 85 more games than Michael Jordan did. Give LeBron the Durability and Longevity Award!

Interesting that KD and Draymond appeared to have a nice exchange, but KD was nicely chiding him for not giving up the ball before traveling. KD is all-time sensitive. He will not be able to get over being called a "b" by an angry Draymond.

If only Tom Brady had Aaron Rodgers' receiving corps & run game. If only Brady had a Davante, a J Graham, an Aaron Jones, a Valdes-Scantling, an Equanimeous, even a Tonyan. If only Brady had a defense like the Pack Sack Attack. (Brady is 7-3, Rodgers 4-4-1 with a loss to Brady).

Aaron Rodgers is on pace to shatter his own NFL record for throwaways. Isn't throwing it away to avoid sacks - still sacked 7th most. He's protecting stats - now 17 TDs to 1 INT. Won't try to make a risky play. Why he's 22nd in QBR and 4-4-1. If he loves it, he cool-whips it.

Aaron Rodgers is the LeBron James of the NFL, so overhyped for spectacular games instead of results. Rodgers played in (and won) one Super Bowl NINE YEARS AGO! Since, he's 5-6 in playoffs. The 5 wins: Joe Webb, Dez catch, KirkCousins, Giants boat trip, Mason Crossbar from 56 & 51
The Rockets look unclogged minus Melo. Still not the defensive team they became last year. But so much freer on offense.
Good throw by Aaron Rodgers to a top 10 receiver. Slightly underthrown. Great concentration by Davante to haul it in despite a near breakup by Shaq Griffin. Huge play.
I love to watch Russell Wilson operate at QB ... unless it's against the Cowboys.

Obviously Mike McCarthy will get blamed for this loss for not challenging the big completion to Lockett, which was not a catch. Look for ARodg to subtly blame him. At this rate McCarthy will be Baker Mayfield's head coach next year.
I wonder how Shannon Sharpe will defend Aaron Rodgers after the Packers punted four times and managed only a field goal in the second half?
